item.title: Moroccan king’s successful heart surgery
item.description: Morocco's King Mohammed VI has successfully undergone heart surgery in the capital Rabat, according to the official MAP news agency.

item.title: India eyes train carriages for virus beds
item.description: India's home minister has offered 500 railway carriages for use as makeshift coronavirus hospital wards as the capital New Delhi struggles to contain a spike in cases.

item.title: HK security law not restrospective: China
item.description: Hong Kong's national security legislation will not punish people retroactively, a senior Chinese official says, touching on a key question raised by residents, diplomats and foreign investors over the controversial law.

item.title: Calls to add 1m to UK virus income schemes
item.description: British finance minister Rishi Sunak must extend the government's already huge coronavirus income support measures to include more than one million additional workers who have missed out, lawmakers said on Monday.

item.title: Russian 16yr jail term for American ‘spy’
item.description: A Russian court has found former United States marine Paul Whelan guilty of spying for Washington, sentencing him to 16 years in jail after a closed trial which US diplomats say had been unfair and opaque.

item.title: Denmark to stimulate virus-hit economy
item.description: Denmark has announced a string of initiatives to stimulate the economy including cash handouts and a fund to support struggling companies as it starts to phase out generous aid packages introduced at the beginning of the coronavirus crisis.

item.title: Russian toll passes 7000, 143 new deaths
item.description: Russia has announced 143 people have died from coronavirus in the past 24 hours.

item.title: Fatal mass wine poisonings in Cambodia
item.description: Cambodian authorities have launched a manhunt for the owner of a business reportedly behind batches of "herbal" rice wine which has poisoned dozens of people and killed at least seven.

item.title: UK, EU agree new momentum needed on talks
item.description: Britain and the EU have agreed new momentum is required in talks on their future ties, supporting plans to intensify negotiations that have all but stalled.

item.title: Irish parties agree on coalition govt deal
item.description: Ireland's Fianna Fail, Fine Gael and Green parties have struck a deal to form a new coalition government which, if ratified by grassroots members, will end a months-long political deadlock.
